node.text: If you’re confused by what is going on in Cuba right now, please take a listen. Cubans have lived without Freedom for long enough. Communism is destroying that country and unfortunately the Cuban government is silencing the people. Make noise. Write to your elected officials. Cubans don’t have a voice right now but we do. I look forward to a day that all Cubans are granted the same rights we are and the world gets to see what makes that country so beautiful. 🇨🇺

node.text:
My brother and I are so excited to be giving away two round trip airline tickets between any two cities in the United States. One lucky winner will get to pick where they want to go and we’ll get them there! We’ll also be announcing a special surprise for the winner on the day of our draw. We’re pretty sure you’re going to like this :)
(Post pandemic of course)

Requirements for entering into this giveaway:
1. Donate $5 to the charity, Pilots For Kids (GoFundMe link is in both of our bios) Edit: Apparently GoFundMe only accepts a minimum of $5 donations. I apologize for this and hope you can still join in!
2. Follow @pilotsforkids 
3. Follow @jettinjack 
4. Comment on this post where you want to go and tag who you’re taking! 

Winner will be randomly chosen and announced Friday 12/18 at 12pm PT! I will DM winner to set up their trip! 

Best of Luck and Happy Holidays! I appreciate all of you more than you’ll ever know ❤️

node.text: If you’re confused by what is going on in Cuba right now, please take a listen. Cubans have lived without Freedom for long enough. Communism is destroying that country and unfortunately the Cuban government is silencing the people. Make noise. Write to your elected officials. Cubans don’t have a voice right now but we do. I look forward to a day that all Cubans are granted the same rights we are and the world gets to see what makes that country so beautiful. 🇨🇺

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Peter Weber in Havana, Cuba. May be an image of text.

node.text: FREE CUBA!! Here’s to this beautiful country turning the page on communism and giving the Cuban people the most precious gift on this planet, FREEDOM! #soscuba

node.text: End of an era right here. I remember running into Chris when I was 18 at the movies. Never imagined all these years later I’d have traveled the world with him and forged such a great friendship. Thank you Chris for your mentorship and for having an impact on so many. The show will never be the same but that’s only a testament to you. Can’t wait to see what you do next my friend!

node.text:
My dream finally came true...
This is one of my first memories of flying with my dad on one of his trips. Ever since, I’ve dreamt of putting on a United Airlines uniform of my own and flying with my dad as his First Officer all around the world. I am so excited to announce that I will officially be joining United Airlines on May 25th!

United is more than just an airline to me, it is family. My parents met aboard a United flight my dad was operating while my mom was a flight attendant. I have memories of having my parents listen and critique my welcome aboard announcement as if I were the Captain of that United flight. Throughout the years, I have joined my dad at the United training center in Denver while he was being checked out in the simulators. The instructors were gracious enough to always let me take the controls of the sim after my dad finished his training, which only deepened my love for aviation even more. You all know flying was my first love, and United is a big reason why. As I begin my career with United I’m hopeful to soon welcome my brother Jack aboard to complete the family legacy and spend a beautiful career flying all around the world together. 

I have to send a huge thank you to Delta Air Lines. You have allowed me to live out my passion and I could not be more grateful for the opportunity you gave me. I have nothing but respect and admiration for the first class operation that you run. I’m so thankful for all the amazing people I had the honor of working with and wish you all the very best! 

I would love to remind all of you to never give up on chasing your dreams and what makes you feel most alive. For a while, it seemed as if mine wouldn’t quite become a reality. If it’s worth it to you though, never ever ever give up on achieving that dream. It will only be that much sweeter in the end. I look forward to welcoming you all aboard the friendly skies soon!

Life's too short not to drink great wine. That why I'm so excited to partner up with Campo Viejo this Mother's Day. I'd like to raise a glass and toast to all the amazing mothers out there and encourage you all to spend some time celebrating the strong mother figures in your lives! And what better way to do that than sitting down with some family recipes, and enjoying a nice glass of @campoviejousa Reserva or Red Blend together! I love you mom ❤️
